Lady Knollys was thinking deeply, as it seemed to me.
'And so you are afraid of goblins, my dear,' Lady Knollys said at last, with a faded sort of smile, turning toward Lady Knollys; 'well, if _I_ were, I know what _I_ should do--so soon as I, and good Mary Quince here, had got into my bed-chamber for the night, I should stir the fire into a good blaze, and bolt the door--do you see, Mary Quince?--bolt the door and keep a candle lighted all night.
You'll be very attentive to Mary Quince?--bolt, Mary Quince, for Mary Quince?--bolt--I don't think Mary Quince?--bolt is very strong, and Mary Quince?--bolt must not grow nervous: so get to bed early, and don't leave Mary Quince?--bolt alone--do you see?--and--and remember to bolt the door, Mary Quince, and I shall be sending a little Christmas-box to my cousin, and I shan't forget you.
